               <floruit notBefore="1800" notAfter="1899">He was a traditional scholar, the popular hero of innumerable Amharic jokes and humorous stories. 
                  He received a thorough church eduction and he held different positions as church administrator, expert in chronology and traditional law (<title ref="LIT1395Fethan"/>), 
                  teacher and advisor. Gabra Ḥannā is said to have penned several religious books; however, none of them has ever been published. 
                  
